During a press briefing, White House Press Secretary Sean Spicer discussed various topics including the recent attack in London, Tech Week at the White House, the President's pro-growth economic message, and the administration's efforts to modernize and streamline the federal government. Spicer also addressed questions about the Russian threat to shoot down American planes over Syria, the President's message to the tech industry, the potential firing of the Deputy Attorney General, and the President's position on climate change and the Paris Agreement. He concluded the briefing by mentioning the President's statement commemorating Juneteenth and the upcoming election in Georgia's sixth district.